Parses command-line arguments and dispatches to the summarizer runner, writing its JSON output to stdout.

Entry point is `dispatch(fs, agent, cli, out)`, which extracts the target paths from `cli.command` (currently only `Paths` variant is implemented), checks that the target count doesn't exceed `MAX_TARGETS` unless `--approve` is set, constructs a `Models` struct with leaf and rollup model names, calls `runner::run()` with those models and the prompt directory, and serializes the result as pretty-printed JSON. All I/O errors — from the agent, filesystem, or writing stdout — are mapped to `SummError::Io`.

The `--leaf-model` and `--rollup-model` arguments are required and must precede the subcommand (clap forbids required global arguments); the `--prompts` directory defaults to `"prompts"` and `--approve` is a cost guard that allows runs over the file limit.